      <odd id="aspace_8225f56d2d73f147b2debceb5207d1f7">
         <head>General note</head>
         <p>Forms part of Yale Record Group 40 (YRG 40), Records of Yale clubs, societies, and organizations.</p>  
      </odd>
      <altformavail id="aspace_5e3c4b31eb8251dec375d673293ecc61">
         <head>Existence and Location of Copies</head>
         <p>A digital reproduction of the Amos Doolittle print, Accession 2005-A-200, can be found in the Manuscripts and Archives Digital Images Database (MADID). A link to MADID can be found on the Manuscripts and Archives web site.</p>  
      </altformavail>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_6425fe084da5afa8ba4ba23b67b50c6f">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The records were a gift of the Elihu Club, 2004. Accession 2005-A-200 on deposit by the Elihu Club, 2005.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_40c6ab203425daecc9ba2ae322e17c8c">
         <head>Conditions Governing Access</head>
         <p>The records are partially restricted. See inventory for details.</p>
         <p>Original born digital files, as well as preservation masters, may not be accessed due to their fragility. Researchers must consult use copies, or if none exist request that they be made. Born digital files cannot be accessed remotely. System requirements include a Manuscripts and Archives computer and file viewing software.</p>  
      </accessrestrict>
      <prefercite id="aspace_b5577593643d02dfc7ebbc33a505536b">
         <head>Preferred Citation</head>
         <p>Elihu Club, Yale University, Records (RU 882). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.</p>  
      </prefercite>
      <processinfo id="aspace_f2ab8afe7d0f4fb4e660a2b3b91fa4e8">
         <head>Processing Information</head>
         <p>Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.</p>  
      </processinfo>
      <arrangement id="aspace_40eba2e6b93b3a114cf2a3d181187f63">
         <head>Arrangement</head>
         <p>The records are arranged by accession.</p>  
      </arrangement>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_8e83d2cee032c5dc8899f6ee45ad01ed">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of photocopies of the Yale Elihu Club constitution, by-laws, correspondence, and member lists, as well as an original print (1791?) by Amos Doolittle.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_0d54946470629e0b7ad56aff06ca4e66">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Elihu Club, a Yale senior society, was established in 1903.</p>  
      </bioghist>
  
